[SN]TITLE[SN]
Motorist, 72, hit with metal pole in 'unprovoked attack' in Birmingham

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 72-year-old man was hit on the head with a metal pole after being chased by a driver in Birmingham, police said.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The victim stopped on Witton Street, Bordesley Green, after being chased by a man in a white Mercedes Sprinter van.
The van driver smashed the front window of the car before attacking the driver.
West Midlands Police it was "unprovoked" and appealed for witnesses to the attack on 8 November to come forward.
